ase for an entirely new concept of prisons and their purpose: an "inner architectonics of reform" that will provide better education for all involved in prisons, more imaginative and careful use of technology, more sophisticated surveillance systems, and better accountability.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Penology.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235296423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300235296.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles